<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-22T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-22T01:00:00-05:00" n="1060" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1060">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8914: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-22T14:00:00+08:00">July 22, 1937—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 22—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>279. The following telegram has been received from the Consulate General
                            at Harbin.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“15, July 21, 3 p.m. Information here is that the Japanese Army in
                                North Manchuria is concentrated in greater strength than are
                                reported on the Soviet border. Russian mechanics in Harbin have been
                                recruited recently in some numbers by the Japanese Army for work
                                near the Russian frontier”.</p>
                        </quote>
                        <p>Repeated to Tokyo, Nanking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>